transcript.text: Hello, thank you for joining us today.
I'm excited to discuss one of the new features called packing slips from our latest version 10.1 of on Print shop.
A packing slip is a comprehensive document that lists all the items included in a package.
In other simpler words, a packing slip is a reflection of all ordered items and is a record of the physical items included on the shipping list.
Also, it allows the buyer or receiver to easily check and verify the received items against the packing slip.
So, how can you utilize this feature?
With our new Packing slip feature, you can now conveniently create and download a complete slip for your orders.
To customize the packing slip, simply navigate to the e-mail notification section and search Packing slip in the search bar.
Here, you can update the content that will be displayed both in the e-mail and in the downloaded packing slips.
Once you have created the format, you can download the slips easily from the Orders section with two convenient methods.
Select the order for which you want to download the packing slips.
Now go to the action button drop down and here you can now find Download packing slip.
When you click on the option, a popup will appear for generating the slips.
Here you have the option to select the order products along with specifying the box count if the order products will be packed in multiple boxes.
Now just click on generate and there you go.
The second way to download the slips is from the Order shipment section.
The download option will be available for the order products for which you have already configured packages.
Let's take a look at how it will appear in the PDF file.
That's it with our new packing slip feature, managing and downloading comprehensive slips for your orders has never been simpler.
For more information and to explore other exciting features of On Print Shop, please visit our website or reach out to our dedicated support team.
Thank you.
